The paper focuses on designing fast and reliable distributed consensus protocols for industrial IoT systems, which involves communication and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with distributed systems and protocols, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the reliability and security of the consensus protocol, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper derives closed-form expressions for end-to-end latency, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
